&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;LEARNING AND DEVELOPMENT – KINGS COURT 1, WORCESTER&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical Practice Facilitator &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;BAND 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;22.5 HOURS PER WEEK - Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Worcestershire Health and Care NHS Trust is committed to learning and development and actively encourages people to make the most of their potential. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have an exciting professional development vacancy for an experienced Registered Nurse, who will be required to have effective professional and inter-professional working relationships to support learning and education for pre-registration nursing students within Worcestershire Health and Care Trust. They will be responsible for providing education and support to ensure that students are fit for practice and purpose.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Clinical Practice Facilitator role supports nursing staff across all of our clinical areas to ensure that our practice supervisors and practice assessors are maintaining a consistent and robust standard. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information please contact Tom Challacombe (Preceptorship &amp; Practice Facilitator) on 07748 646147 or via &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;thomas.challacombe@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
